headlines.description: — Josh Hart had 20 points, 19 rebounds and 10 assists in his fourth triple-double of the season, OG Anunoby scored 14 points in his return from an 18-game absence and the New York Knicks beat the Philadelphia 76ers 106-79 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anunoby returns, Hart delivers another triple-double as the Knicks rout the 76ers 106-79

headlines.description: — Trey Jemison scored a career-high 24 points, GG Jackson added 19 and the Memphis Grizzlies used a late rally to hold on for a 109-97 victory over the Washington Wizards on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trey Jemison scores career-high 24 points to lead Grizzlies past Wizards, 109-97

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Myles Turner bristled when a reporter suggested that Indiana's win over Oklahoma City should be considered a big deal.
headlines.shortLinkText: Turner scores 24, leads Pacers in 121-111 win over West-leading Thunder

events.name: Houston Rockets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet scored 21 points and the Houston Rockets held Victor Wembanyama in check to beat the San Antonio Spurs 103-101 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet scores 21 points and Rockets hold off Spurs 103-101 on an off night for Wembanyama

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 38 points and Derrick White added 24 to lead the Boston Celtics to a 123-107 win over the struggling Utah Jazz on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 38 and Celtics use 20-0 run to get past Jazz 123-107

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 37 points, Nickeil Alexander-Walker added a season-high 28 and the Minnesota Timberwolves roared back from an early 22-point deficit for a 118-100 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards leads big comeback, Kawhi Leonard injured in Timberwolves' 118-100 win over Clippers

headlines.description: — De'Aaron Fox scored 29 points and the Sacramento Kings beat Milwaukee 129-94 on Tuesday night for their first win over the Bucks in more than eight years.
headlines.shortLinkText: De'Aaron Fox scores 29 points and the Kings snap a 15-game skid against the Bucks with a 129-94 win
